sd=Customer Surveys	Define and execute and analyze customer surveys	A bank develops a customer questionnaire to obtain feedback from customers that make frequent use of the self-service contact center facility for service improvement suggestions	Handle the deployment, execution and on-going refinement of customer surveys. This includes many types of survey including traditional mailshot questionnaires, in production review/feedback solicitation, review panels/focus groups. The survey execution process performs the survey definitions, selection of reviewers, surveying and post survey analysis
sdpath=customer-surveys
crpath=customer-survey-procedure
crr=Customer Survey Procedure Instance
mcr=Customer Survey Procedure
bqs=Definition ReviewerSelection Execution SurveyAnalysis
CONFIG
CustomerSurveyProcedure	initiate	Initiate customer survey processing		initiateCustomerSurveyProcedure		#desc
CustomerSurveyProcedure	update	Update details of an active customer survey process		updateCustomerSurveyProcedure		#desc
CustomerSurveyProcedure	control	Control the execution of a customer survey (e.g. suspend processing)		controlCustomerSurveyProcedure		#desc
CustomerSurveyProcedure	request	Request manual intervention to the survey process (e.g. revise customer targeting criteria)		requestCustomerSurveyProcedure		#desc
CustomerSurveyProcedure	retrieve	Retrieve details about a customer survey process		retrieveCustomerSurveyProcedure		#desc
